<br>
This one is of strong spirit, The Harvester thought to himself. Focused he is. Ah, but young. Young and eager to make hs mark on the world. Yes, make a mark he shall...a scar he will etch into the lives of his loved ones. The Harvester's hideous mouth curled into a cruel sneer. Sensing his target, the Harvester made his way towards Lake Rathetear. <br>
<br>
Arikel and Zariel were sparring in the Arena, Arikel teaching his little sister the proper technique of the &quot;Eagle Strike&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;No, Zariel. Arch your hand like this!&quot; Arikel yelled.<br>
&quot;Ari, I'm trying,&quot; Zariel said, defending herself.<br>
&quot;Try it again!&quot;<br>
<br>
Zariel took her stance and in one blindingly quick movement, performed the manuever.<br>
<br>
&quot;I did it, Ari!&quot; she shouted with glee.<br>
<br>
Arikel didn't look impressed, &quot;I expect nothing less Zariel, from a monk and from my sister.&quot;<br>
<br>
The joy in Zariel's face faded. &quot;Ari...&quot;<br>
<br>
A cold chill shook the two monks bodies making the hair on their arms stand on end.<br>
<br>
&quot;Did you feel that Ari?&quot; Zariel asked with a shiver.<br>
<br>
Arikel glared at her. &quot;A monk must remain focused from the inconviences of the outside world Zariel.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ari, what's wro..&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;FOCUS!&quot; Arikel shouted. <br>
&quot;We must be stronger than our enemies, stronger then our friends!&quot; <br>
Arikel circled his sister as he spoke. &quot;The elves, the dwarves, the gnomes, the halflings, all of them lack the discipline that we have! Where they have failed, we have strived! We've spread across Norrath uniting the good races, while they were busy argueing. We are what's right!&quot;<br>
<br>
Zariel was stunned, why was her brother so angry? <br>
&quot;Arikel, they are our friends.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Friends! They care NOTHING for us!&quot; Arikel exploded. <br>
&quot;They are weak, they need us to survive Zariel! We are the power!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;No you're wrong, acting together has made our races strive.&quot; she meekly replied.<br>
<br>
Arikel's face went red with rage, his hands balling up into fists as he approached his sibling.<br>
<br>
&quot;You dare stand to correct me?&quot;<br>
<br>
